Pop your kettle on to boil. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small pieces. Trim the @spring onion{1} and thinly slice. Halve the @red chilli{1/2} lengthways, deseed then finely chop. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all). Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. Add the pepper, garlic, chilli and half the spring onion. Stir and cook for ~{2%minutes}, then add the @red Thai style paste{50%g} and stir together.

> Tip: Add less chilli if you don't like spice!

After ~{1%minute}, pour in the @coconut milk{200%ml} and mix until smooth. Add the @chicken stock powder{1} with the @water{400%ml}(boiling from your kettle) and bring to a simmer.

Add the @peanut butter{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @?sugar{1%pinch} (if you have some) to your pan. Simmer gently for ~{10%minutes}. Taste the laksa and add seasoning if you think it needs it - salt, pepper, sugar - whatever suits your taste!

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and lime zest. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Stir-fry until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. When cooked, remove to a #plate{} and cover with foil to keep warm.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

When the laksa has been cooking for 10 mins, add in the @egg noodle nest{2}. Cook until soft enough to eat, about ~{4%minutes}.

> Tip: The noodles may soak up some of the coconutty liquid. If this is the case, just add a splash of water to get it back to a soupy consistency.

Add the chicken to the pan and simmer until the chicken is piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat and add half the lime juice. Taste and add salt, pepper and more lime juice if you feel it needs it. Serve in big #bowls{} topped with the coriander and the remaining spring onion. Enjoy!

> Step 4 MOD: If you've chosen diced chicken breast instead of diced chicken thigh, just cook the diced breast in the same way the recipe tells you to cook the diced thigh in the step above and in the rest of the recipe.